Personal Notes: This Doom moves shooters forward in a direction that I really really hope other developers take. Every component of your move set is so neatly designed to encourage the flow of always moving, always ripping and tearing. There’s a learning curve to almost every single enemy, which is further promoted by the weak points they have. Slayer gates end up being the most fun challenges in the game because of the mix of enemies you have to take on, rather than just being a test of mindlessly shooting.
